{{Quote|Hang on. We're ''freelancers''. One gig at a time. No exclusive contracts.|Chilla Zin|<ref name="Vader 18" />}}
The '''Assassin's Guild''',<ref name="Vader 20">[[Darth Vader (2020) 20|''Darth Vader'' (2020) 20]]</ref> also known as the '''Assassins Guild''',<ref name="Vader 18" /> the '''Assassin Guild''',<ref name="Bounty Hunters 42">[[Bounty Hunters 42|''Bounty Hunters'' 42]]</ref> or as the '''league''',<ref name="Vader 17">[[Darth Vader (2020) 17|''Darth Vader'' (2020) 17]]</ref> was an organization active during the [[Imperial Era]], the members of which were [[Mercenary|freelance]] [[assassin]]s.<ref name="Vader 18" /> Prior to entering the service of [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]], [[Ochi|Ochi of Bestoon]] was a [[Master Assassin]] of the league.<ref name="Vader 17" /> Sometime later, [[Chilla Zin]], [[G-90|Gee-Ninety]], and [[Loriach]], three members of the Guild, were hired by Ochi, now a [[Sith assassin]] and a servant of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith|Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]], to [[Assassination on Vincorba|assassinate]] a [[Unidentified pontiff|pontiff]] allied with the [[Crimson Dawn]] criminal syndicate on [[Vincorba]]. After the three performed the job, they were confronted by Ochi and Vader, who revealed that the job had been a test so that they could serve Vader in his quest to destroy Crimson Dawn.<ref name="Vader 18" />

